---
description: Supabase usage and safety rules
globs: ["src/lib/supabase/**/*.ts", "src/app/**/*.ts", "src/app/**/*.tsx", "proxy.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Supabase rules:

- Use `@supabase/ssr` patterns for browser and server clients.
- Keep browser and server client creation separate.
- Never use the service role key in browser code.
- Assume Row Level Security is enabled for app data.
- Prefer server-side access for privileged reads/writes.
- Put schema changes in migrations, not only in the dashboard.
- When adding tables or policies, note the required RLS behavior.
- Keep auth callback and token refresh flows simple and explicit.
- Do not scatter Supabase initialization logic across files.
